#. <section class="sutta" id="an9.34"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an9.34:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 9"
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 9"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "an9.34:0.2"
msgid "4. Mahāvagga"
msgstr "4. The Greater Chapter"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "an9.34:0.3"
msgid "34. Nibbānasukhasutta"
msgstr "34. Extinguishment is Bliss"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi4.415"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "an9.34:1.1"
msgid ""
"Ekaṃ samayaṃ āyasmā sāriputto rājagahe viharati veḷuvane kalandakanivāpe."
msgstr ""
"At one time Venerable Sāriputta was staying near Rājagaha, in the Bamboo "
"Grove, the squirrels’ feeding ground."

msgctxt "an9.34:1.2"
msgid "Tatra kho āyasmā sāriputto bhikkhū āmantesi:"
msgstr "There he addressed the mendicants:"

msgctxt "an9.34:1.3"
msgid "“sukhamidaṃ, āvuso, nibbānaṃ."
msgstr "“Reverends, extinguishment is bliss!"

msgctxt "an9.34:1.4"
msgid "Sukhamidaṃ, āvuso, nibbānan”ti."
msgstr "Extinguishment is bliss!”"

msgctxt "an9.34:1.5"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, āyasmā udāyī āyasmantaṃ sāriputtaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr "When he said this, Venerable Udāyī said to him:"

# This phrase reads much better when interpreted as locative of reference.
msgctxt "an9.34:1.6"
msgid "“kiṃ panettha, āvuso sāriputta, sukhaṃ yadettha natthi vedayitan”ti?"
msgstr ""
"“But Reverend Sāriputta, what’s blissful about it, since nothing is felt?”"

msgctxt "an9.34:1.7"
msgid "“Etadeva khvettha, āvuso, sukhaṃ yadettha natthi vedayitaṃ."
msgstr "“The fact that nothing is felt is precisely what’s blissful about it."

msgctxt "an9.34:1.8"
msgid "Pañcime, āvuso, kāmaguṇā."
msgstr "Reverend, there are these five kinds of sensual stimulation."

msgctxt "an9.34:1.9"
msgid "Katame pañca?"
msgstr "What five?"

msgctxt "an9.34:1.10"
msgid ""
"Cakkhuviññeyyā rūpā iṭṭhā kantā manāpā piyarūpā kāmūpasaṃhitā rajanīyā, "
msgstr ""
"Sights known by the eye that are likable, desirable, agreeable, pleasant, "
"sensual, and arousing. "

msgctxt "an9.34:1.11"
msgid "sotaviññeyyā saddā … pe …"
msgstr "Sounds known by the ear …"

msgctxt "an9.34:1.12"
msgid "ghānaviññeyyā gandhā …"
msgstr "Smells known by the nose …"

msgctxt "an9.34:1.13"
msgid "jivhāviññeyyā rasā …"
msgstr "Tastes known by the tongue …"

msgctxt "an9.34:1.14"
msgid ""
"kāyaviññeyyā phoṭṭhabbā iṭṭhā kantā manāpā piyarūpā kāmūpasaṃhitā rajanīyā—"
msgstr ""
"Touches known by the body that are likable, desirable, agreeable, pleasant, "
"sensual, and arousing."

msgctxt "an9.34:1.15"
msgid "ime kho, āvuso, pañca kāmaguṇā."
msgstr "These are the five kinds of sensual stimulation."

msgctxt "an9.34:1.16"
msgid ""
"Yaṃ kho, āvuso, ime pañca kāmaguṇe paṭicca uppajjati sukhaṃ somanassaṃ, idaṃ "
"vuccatāvuso, kāmasukhaṃ."
msgstr ""
"The pleasure and happiness that arise from these five kinds of sensual "
"stimulation is called sensual pleasure."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "an9.34:2.1"
msgid ""
"Idhāvuso, bhikkhu vivicceva kāmehi … pe … paṭhamaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja "
"viharati."
msgstr ""
"First, take a mendicant who, quite secluded from sensual pleasures … enters "
"and remains in the first absorption."

msgctxt "an9.34:2.2"
msgid ""
"Tassa ce, āvuso, bhikkhuno iminā vihārena viharato kāmasahagatā "
"saññāmanasikārā samudācaranti, svassa hoti ābādho."
msgstr ""
"While a mendicant is in such a meditation, should perceptions and attentions "
"accompanied by sensual pleasures beset them, that’s an affliction for them."

msgctxt "an9.34:2.3"
msgid "Seyyathāpi, āvuso, sukhino dukkhaṃ uppajjeyya yāvadeva ābādhāya;"
msgstr ""
"Suppose a happy person were to experience pain; that would be an affliction "
"for them."

msgctxt "an9.34:2.4"
msgid ""
"evamevassa te kāmasahagatā saññāmanasikārā samudācaranti. Svassa hoti ābādho."
msgstr ""
"In the same way, should perceptions and attentions accompanied by sensual "
"pleasures beset them, that’s an affliction for them."

msgctxt "an9.34:2.5"
msgid "Yo kho panāvuso, ābādho dukkhametaṃ vuttaṃ bhagavatā."
msgstr "And affliction has been called suffering by the Buddha."

msgctxt "an9.34:2.6"
msgid ""
"Imināpi kho etaṃ, āvuso, pariyāyena veditabbaṃ yathā sukhaṃ nibbānaṃ. (1)"
msgstr "That’s the way to understand how extinguishment is bliss."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi4.416"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "an9.34:3.1"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, āvuso, bhikkhu vitakkavicārānaṃ vūpasamā … pe … dutiyaṃ jhānaṃ "
"upasampajja viharati."
msgstr ""
"Furthermore, take a mendicant who, as the placing of the mind and keeping it "
"connected are stilled, enters and remains in the second absorption."

msgctxt "an9.34:3.2"
msgid ""
"Tassa ce, āvuso, bhikkhuno iminā vihārena viharato vitakkasahagatā "
"saññāmanasikārā samudācaranti, svassa hoti ābādho."
msgstr ""
"While a mendicant is in such a meditation, should perceptions and attentions "
"accompanied by placing of the mind and keeping it connected beset them, that’"
"s an affliction for them."

msgctxt "an9.34:3.3"
msgid "Seyyathāpi, āvuso, sukhino dukkhaṃ uppajjeyya yāvadeva ābādhāya;"
msgstr ""
"Suppose a happy person were to experience pain; that would be an affliction "
"for them."

msgctxt "an9.34:3.4"
msgid ""
"evamevassa te vitakkasahagatā saññāmanasikārā samudācaranti. Svassa hoti "
"ābādho."
msgstr ""
"In the same way, should perceptions and attentions accompanied by placing of "
"the mind and keeping it connected beset them, that’s an affliction for them."

msgctxt "an9.34:3.5"
msgid "Yo kho panāvuso, ābādho dukkhametaṃ vuttaṃ bhagavatā."
msgstr "And affliction has been called suffering by the Buddha."

msgctxt "an9.34:3.6"
msgid ""
"Imināpi kho etaṃ, āvuso, pariyāyena veditabbaṃ yathā sukhaṃ nibbānaṃ. (2)"
msgstr "That too is a way to understand how extinguishment is bliss."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "an9.34:4.1"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, āvuso, bhikkhu pītiyā ca virāgā … pe … tatiyaṃ jhānaṃ "
"upasampajja viharati."
msgstr ""
"Furthermore, take a mendicant who, with the fading away of rapture, enters "
"and remains in the third absorption."

msgctxt "an9.34:4.2"
msgid ""
"Tassa ce, āvuso, bhikkhuno iminā vihārena viharato pītisahagatā "
"saññāmanasikārā samudācaranti, svassa hoti ābādho."
msgstr ""
"While a mendicant is in such a meditation, should perceptions and attentions "
"accompanied by rapture beset them, that’s an affliction for them."

msgctxt "an9.34:4.3"
msgid "Seyyathāpi, āvuso, sukhino dukkhaṃ uppajjeyya yāvadeva ābādhāya;"
msgstr ""
